	(254,NULL,NULL,2,'Frankie & Bennys','frankie_bennys','Â£5 off when you spend Â£20','<h2 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; line-height: 24.959999084472656px;\">&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.6em 0px 1.2em; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20.399999618530273px;\">Rumour has it that Frankie Giuliani was 10 years old when, with his Mamma and Poppa, he left Sicily and landed at Ellis Island, New York in 1924.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.6em 0px 1.2em; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20.399999618530273px;\">They moved in with relatives in &lsquo;Little Italy&rsquo;, a predominantly Italian neighbourhood. Poppa soon found work, but from the home country he\'d brought a little money and a lot of ambition. It was no surprise then, when the family opened a restaurant within a year, everybody was helping with the building and the cooking in equal measure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.6em 0px 1.2em; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20.399999618530273px;\">Each of them had a favourite dish to contribute, but it was Mamma\'s home-style cooking that was the base from which the business prospered. Frankie went to the nearby High School and became lifetime friends with Benny, already a third generation American.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.6em 0px 1.2em; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20.399999618530273px;\">In 1953 Poppa retired and Frankie and Benny took over the business, combining the best of popular American food with traditional Italian dishes. The rest, as they say, is history...</p>','','BS4 3EN','51.4426688','-2.5683698999999933',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'2014-07-10 00:00:01','2014-07-01 00:00:01','2014-07-10 04:12:59',0),
	(256,NULL,47,2,'John Shuttleworth','john_shuttleworth','Versatile singer/organist, John Shuttleworth, wants to share fond memories of his favourite past weekends.','<p><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.799999237060547px;\">Versatile singer/organist, John Shuttleworth, wants to share fond memories of his favourite past weekends. However, a typo on the poster means John is obliged to spend the evening paying homage to his next-door neighbour and sole agent - the diminutive Ken Worthington. He\'ll probably end up doing both!&nbsp;</span><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: #990033; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #666666; text-decoration: none; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" href=\"http://www.tobaccofactorytheatres.com/shows/detail/john_shuttleworth_a_wee_ken_to_remember\">more info...</a></p>','','Bs31jp','51.4422212','-2.614305599999966',NULL,NULL,1,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,'2014-07-01 00:00:01','2014-07-01 00:00:01','2014-07-14 10:38:30',0),
	(257,NULL,40,2,'Mimic','mimic','Poetic and prescient, this virtuosic solo performance from Raymond Scannell (Infinite Lives)','<p><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.799999237060547px;\">Poetic and prescient, this virtuosic solo performance from Raymond Scannell (Infinite Lives), tells the story of Julian Neary, whose childhood gift for mimicry &ndash; from Columbo and Jimmy Stewart to Billie Holiday and Morrissey &ndash; becomes his ticket out of 1980s Ireland, until the chaos he sees in the outside world reflects his own chaos within.&nbsp;</span><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: #990033; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #666666; text-decoration: none; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" href=\"http://www.tobaccofactorytheatres.com/shows/detail/mimic\">more info...</a></p>','','Bs31jp','51.4422212','-2.614305599999966',NULL,NULL,1,0,1,0,NULL,NULL,'2014-07-01 00:00:01','2014-07-01 00:00:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0),
	(259,NULL,39,2,'Stalin\'s daughter','stalins_daughter','The incredible true story of how Josef Stalinâ€™s daughter came to make her new life in Clifton, Bristol.','<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">The incredible true story of how Josef Stalin&rsquo;s daughter came to make her new life in Clifton, Bristol.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">They never ask me who I am, or why I came. Only when I plan on leaving.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Leaving three husbands and the fall of the Soviet Union in her wake, Svetlana Alliluyeva seeks a place to reflect on the horrors of her past and to escape her father&rsquo;s name.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">After defecting to the United States, she assumes a new name, Lana Peters, before moving on to England. To Bristol. To Clifton. But a new name doesn&rsquo;t give you a new identity. Whether she calls herself Svetlana or Lana, she is still Stalin&rsquo;s daughter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">David Lane&rsquo;s previous work includes the Meyer-Whitworth nominated<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">BEGIN/END</em>&nbsp;and he is the author of Contemporary British Drama.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #333333; font-family: \'Lucida Sans\', Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 16.799999237060547px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Bristol based Blue Brook Productions is led by Kevin Cattell and Ed Viney. Their previous productions have included the sell-out shows&nbs